 <body>
  <h1>
   mouse_x
  </h1>
  This
  <b>
   read-only
  </b>
  variable returns the current x axis position of the mouse within the room.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">mouse_x;
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">x = median(64, mouse_x, room_width - 64);
</code></pre>
  The above code will maintain the instance at the mouse x position as long as it is within the limits of 64 pixels from either side of the room.
 </body>
